A PCB that adds some feature to a computer

Usually connected to a [[PCI Slot]] or [[PCIe Slot]] (Peripheral Component Interconnect)
- [![upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/67/PCI_Sl...](data:image/jpeg;base64,)]
- [[PCIe Slot]]: more modern
	- not parallel, serial instead
	- specified number of names
		- x1, x2, x4, etc

Note: now usually extra features integrated into motherboard or other components

Examples:
- [[Graphics Card (GPU)]]
	- Discrete graphics card (not integrated graphics)
	- Will have HDMI interface that you connect monitor with
- [[Sound Card]]: sound input/output (headphone jacks etc.)
- [[Capture Card]]: input videos (HDMI)
- [[Network Interface Card (NIC)]]
	- [![Amazon.com: 10/100/1000Mbps Gigabit Ethernet PCI Express NIC Network Card |  with Intel I210 Chip | Ethernet Server Converged Network Adapter | Single  RJ45 Port | PCI Express 2.1 X1 | Compare to Intel I210-T1 : Electronics](data:image/jpeg;base64,)]
	- Every device on network has a NIC
		- Often built into motherboard
		- Many options: fiber, copper, etc
- [[Expansion Cards]]
	- [![8-Port USB PCIe Expansion Card, Industrial Grade USB](https://advdownload.blob.core.windows.net/productfile/PIS/PCE-USB/Product%20-%20Photo(Main)/PCE-USB4_3D_S20160307153958.jpg)![8-Port USB PCIe Expansion Card, Industrial Grade USB](data:image/jpeg;base64,)]
